commit.message: Relax upper bound of text, allow text-2.1
Use wikilink syntax in doc strings to mark the `Doc` type

Require hslua 2.3, tasty-lua 1.1

This adds typing information to fields, and links the Doc type to the
module.
CI: use latest versions of third-party actions
Drop support for GHC older than 8.4
Use common stanza to dry up the cabal file
CI: add GHC 9.2.2 to test matrix

Changes to allow doclayout 0.4 (#1)

* Allow doclayout 0.4

* Comment out test that fails with doclayout < 0.4.

commit.message:
Relax upper bound for hslua

Allow hslua-2.2.0.
Ensure all function parameters have a description
Add more methods to type Doc

Ensure main document is always the first function argument

Makes it easier to use functions as methods.

Add methods to type Doc

Functions that take a `Doc` as their first argument are added as methods
for convenience.
